import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['year'])
    data = data.sort_values(by='year')
    data = data.groupby(['sex', 'job'])['job_count'].sum().reset_index()

    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    width = 0.35
    x = data['sex'].unique()
    for i, job in enumerate(data['job'].unique()):
        job_data = data[data['job'] == job]
        ax.bar(x + (i - 1/2) * width, job_data['job_count'], width, label=job)

    ax.set_ylabel('Job Count')
    ax.set_xlabel('Sex')
    ax.set_xticks(x)
    ax.set_xticklabels(['Female', 'Male'])
    ax.legend(title='Job')

    plt.title('What is the distribution of job count by sex?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='count', ascending=False).head(10)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.barh(data['job'], data['count'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Count')
    ax.set_ylabel('Job')
    ax.set_title('What are the top 10 jobs by count?')
    for i, v in enumerate(data['count']):
        ax.text(v + 3, i + .25, str(v), color='blue', fontweight='bold')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='year')
    data = data.set_index('year')
    data = data.pivot(columns='job', values='perc')
    data.plot(kind='area', stacked=True)
    plt.title('What is the percentage distribution of job count by year?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by=['job', 'sex'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    width = 0.35
    ax.bar(data['job'] + width/2, data['job_count'], width, label='Job Count')
    ax.bar(data['job'] + width/2, data['count'] - data['job_count'], width, bottom=data['job_count'], label='Other Jobs')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    ax.set_xlabel('Job and Sex')
    ax.set_xticks(data['job'].unique())
    ax.set_xticklabels(data['job'].unique())
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of job count by job and sex?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
